{
    "_comment": "Each grade is {radial, axial, slot}. 'radial' = half-extra on diameter (all features); 'axial' = along-axis allowance; 'slot' = additional half-width for narrow + cross slots (FDM tightens narrow slots more than the round envelope). 'slot' is OPTIONAL and overridable per grade — an omitted key loads as 0.0. The shipped machine_profiles.json already carries a conservative slip.slot = 0.10 for fdm_standard, so most users only calibrate slip.radial. Override 'slot' here only on an unusual printer. (This _comment key is not a real profile; the loader ignores it.)",
